label.value: Stage MS Childhood Neuroblastoma by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Metastatic disease confined to skin, liver, and/or bone marrow, in a patient less than 18 months (547 days). MIBG scintigraphy must be negative in bone and bone marrow. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) protocol. It is based on findings at surgery for patients who have received chemotherapy prior to surgery. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 1, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the tier 1 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) protocol.

label.value: Localized Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Tumor confined to area of origin including abdominal lymph nodes. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Metastatic Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Distant metastases present at diagnosis. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Swi3p

value.value: Nuclear Swi3p is an 825-aa, 93-kD general RNA polymerase II transcription factor component of the SWI/SNF nucleosome/chromatin remodeling complex involved in global transcriptional activation of induced gene expression. This complex alters chromatin structure to facilitate binding of gene-specific transcription factors. Swi3p contains a MYB-like domain and interacts with the N-terminus of SNF2. (from Swiss-Prot, SGD, and NCI)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the tier 2 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) protocol.

label.value: Stage y-I Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Tumor limited to kidney and completely resected. Renal capsule may be infiltrated by tumor, but tumor does not reach the outer surface. Tumor may protrude or bulge into the pelvic system or ureter but does not infiltrate. Vessel of renal sinus not involved. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage y-II Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Tumor extends beyond kidney but completely resected. Tumor penetrates renal capsule into perirenal fat. Tumor infiltrates the renal sinus and/or invades blood and lymphatic vessels outside renal parenchyma but is completely resected. Tumor infiltrates adjacent organs or vena cava but is completely resected. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage y-III Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Incomplete excision of the tumor (gross or microscopic extension beyond the resection margins). Involved abdominal lymph nodes, including necrotic tumor or chemotherapy-induced changes. Tumor rupture before or intraoperatively. Tumor has penetrated the peritoneal surface. Tumor thrombi present at resection margins. Surgical biopsy prior to resection (does not include needle biopsy). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage IV Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, International Society of Pediatric Oncology (SIOP) Protocol

value.value: Hematogenous metastases or spread beyond abdomen at diagnosis. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) protocol. It is based on findings at surgery for patients who have not received chemotherapy prior to surgery. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 1, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the tier 1 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) protocol.

label.value: Localized Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Tumor confined to area of origin including abdominal lymph nodes. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Metastatic Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Distant metastases present at diagnosis. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the tier 2 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) protocol.

label.value: SNF6

value.value: A component of the SWI/SNF global transcription activator complex, SNF6 assists gene-specific activators through nucleosome/chromatin remodeling.  The SWI/SNF complex is required for induced expression of many genes and alters chromatin structure to facilitate binding of gene-specific dedicated transcription factors.  SNF6 is a non-specific RNA polymerase II transcription factor.  (from SWISS-PROT P18888, SGD S0001017, and NCI)

label.value: Age at Last Exposure

value.value: Age of subject at the last known exposure to a hazardous factor or substance.

label.value: Cancer Detection Method

value.value: The observational modality that was utilized to detect the cancer.

label.value: Chemical Exposure Type Indicator

value.value: An indicator specifying the chemical or chemical class to which a subject was exposed.

label.value: Number of Days Between Index Date and First Event

value.value: The number of days between an index date and the date of the first reported event following treatment.

label.value: Number of Days Between Index Date and Risk Factor Diagnosis

value.value: The number of days between an index date and the date that an individual is diagnosed with a specific risk factor.

label.value: Disease Progression Evidence

value.value: The clinical or laboratory test result that was the basis for a progressive disease finding.

label.value: Stage I Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Tumor is limited to the kidney and completely excised. Renal capsule intact, not penetrated by tumor. No tumor invasion of veins or lymphatics of renal sinus. No nodal or hematogenous metastases. No prior biopsy. Negative margins. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage II Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Tumor extends beyond kidney but completely resected. Tumor penetrates renal capsule. Tumor in lymphatics or veins of renal sinus. Tumor in renal vein with margin not involved. No nodal or hematogenous metastases. Negative margins. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage III Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Residual tumor or nonhematogenous metastases confined to abdomen. Involved abdominal nodes. Peritoneal contamination or tumor implant. Tumor spillage of any degree occurring before or during surgery. Gross residual tumor in abdomen. Biopsy of tumor (including fine-needle aspiration) prior to removal of kidney. Resection margins involved by tumor. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Cost for Patients Questionnaire

value.value: A questionnaire designed to assess an individual's expenses as a result of their state of health. It includes questions about out-of-pocket costs, time required for travel or for booking medical services, and loss of income.

label.value: Autologous-Cell Melanoma Vaccine

value.value: An autologous-cell vaccine for melanoma.

label.value: DRD2 2 Allele

value.value: Human DRD2 Gene at 11q23 encodes Dopamine Receptor D2, a G-protein coupled receptor that inhibits adenylyl cyclase activity. Missense mutation in DRD2 causes myoclonus dystonia; other mutations have been associated with schizophrenia. Alternative splicing results in two different isoforms. A third variant has been described, but it has not been determined whether this form is normal or due to aberrant splicing. Different alleles are associated with increased incidence of substance abuse. (NCI)

label.value: Stage IV Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2, Children's Oncology Group (COG) Protocol

value.value: Hematogenous metastases or spread beyond abdomen at diagnosis. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Extracapsular Extent Indicator

value.value: An indication of whether the extent of tumor invasion through an organ capsule is focal or extensive, or if it was not reported.

label.value: Travel Question

value.value: A question regarding travel by an individual.

label.value: Childhood Malignant Kidney Neoplasm Excluding Renal Cell Carcinoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood malignant kidney neoplasms excluding renal cell carcinoma, according to the Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2.

label.value: Paid for Accommodations When Travelling to Health Center or Consultations

value.value: A question about whether an individual paid for accommodations when travelling to a health center or to consultations.

label.value: Renovated Home to Accommodate Condition

value.value: A question about whether an individual renovated their home to better accommodate their condition.

label.value: First Post-treatment Event

value.value: The first clincally-relevant event following treatment.

label.value: Expense Question

value.value: A question about the costs or expenses for an individual's healthcare.

label.value: Number of Treated Lesions

value.value: The number of lesions subjected to treatment.

label.value: Second Degree Relative

value.value: Any relative who is two meioses away from a particular individual in a family; a relative with whom one quarter of an individual's genes is shared (i.e., grandparent, grandchild, uncle, aunt, nephew, niece, half-sibling) (from Genetics Home Reference glossary)

label.value: Paid for Additional Non-Medical Services

value.value: A question about whether an individual paid for additional non-medical services during or following their consultations.

label.value: Incurred Other Expenses Related to Accessing Health Care Services

value.value: A question about whether an individual incurred other expenses related to accessing health care services.

label.value: Incurred Expenses for Purchase of Medical Devices

value.value: A question about whether an individual incurred expenses for the purchase of medical devices.

label.value: Incurred Expenses for Home Care Services

value.value: A question about whether an individual  incurred expenses for home care services.

label.value: Paid for Non-Medical Care Services

value.value: A question about whether an individual paid for non-medical care services.

label.value: Paid for Dependent Care

value.value: A question about whether an individual paid for care of dependents or pets.

label.value: Did Someone Accompany You to Health Center or Consultations

value.value: A question about whether an individual had a caregiver or someone else accompany them to the health center or consultations.

label.value: Travelled Together with a Caregiver or Companion to Health Center

value.value: A question about whether an individual travelled together with caregiver or accompanying person to the health center.

label.value: Did Companion Pay for Accommodations

value.value: A question about whether an individual's companion had to paid for accommodations.

label.value: Caregiver or Companion Incurred Other Expenses

value.value: A question about whether an individual's companion incurred any other expenses.

label.value: Xenograft Model

value.value: An experimental system in which (usually) human tumor cells are transplanted into immunocompromised mice that do not reject human cells; cells may be implanted under the skin or into the organ type in which the tumor originated. These model systems may be used for drug development and studies of molecular biological mechanisms of cancer.
